===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|alt=𢫏,搇,𠖫,扻-to slap}}
Traditionally related to {{zh-l|𠖫|to cover}} ({{zh-ref|Bai, 1980}}; {{zh-ref|You, 1992}}).

{{zh-ref|Bauer (1996)}} considers this to be part of an area word family in Southeast Asian languages: ''*khVm ~ *khVp ~ *kVm ~ *kVp ~ *k(h)l/rm/p''. It is probably related to {{zh-l|扱|kap1|to cover; to imprint}}. Compare {{cog|nan|-}} {{zh-l|崁|khàm|to cover}}, {{cog|my|ခြုံ||to cover; to wrap}}, {{cog|tai-pro|*hɤmᴮ||to cover (with cloth)}} (whence {{cog|za|hoemq}} and {{cog|th|ห่ม}}). The root is found in many Sinitic dialects including Cantonese, Hakka, Hokkien and Wenzhounese.

